<doc>
  <member name="DXGI_RESIDENCY">
    <summary>
      <para>Flags indicating the memory location of a resource.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This enum is used by <see cref="QueryResourceResidency" />.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3ddxgi/d3d10-graphics-reference-dxgi-enums">DXGI Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="DXGI_RESIDENCY.DXGI_RESIDENCY_FULLY_RESIDENT">
    <summary>
      <para>The resource is located in video memory.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DXGI_RESIDENCY.DXGI_RESIDENCY_RESIDENT_IN_SHARED_MEMORY">
    <summary>
      <para>At least some of the resource is located in CPU memory.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="DXGI_RESIDENCY.DXGI_RESIDENCY_EVICTED_TO_DISK">
    <summary>
      <para>At least some of the resource has been paged out to the hard drive.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>